---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
	title="OpenAttitude"
	description="Cockpit panels for flight simulators like FlightGear  — Vue 3, live properties, and npm instrument packages."
>
	<section
		class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-slate-800 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900/50 to-slate-950"
	>
		<div
			class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_80%_50%_at_50%_-20%,rgba(34,211,238,0.12),transparent)]"
		>
		</div>
		<div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 sm:py-28">
			<p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-cyan-400/90">FlightGear · Web panels</p>
			<h1 class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl">
				Flight Simulator cockpits in the browser
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
				<strong class="text-slate-200">OpenAttitude</strong> ships a full <strong class="text-slate-200"
					>Vue 3</strong
				>
				panel with steam-style gauges, a <strong class="text-slate-200">Leaflet</strong> GPS map, and a <strong
					class="text-slate-200">WebSocket</strong
				> link to FlightGear’s PropertyListener—plus reusable
				<code class="rounded bg-slate-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-cyan-300/90">@openattitude/*</code> instruments
				on npm.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
				<a
					href="https://senecaii.openattitude.org"
					class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-cyan-500 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 no-underline shadow-lg shadow-cyan-500/25 transition hover:bg-cyan-400"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					Open live panel
				</a>
				<a
					href="/docs"
					class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-slate-600 bg-slate-900/50 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white no-underline transition hover:border-slate-500 hover:bg-slate-800"
				>
					Read the docs
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 sm:py-20">
		<h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold text-white sm:text-3xl">Why this stack</h2>
		<p class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-2xl text-center text-slate-400">
			Separate the <em>shell</em> (GPL panel app) from <em>libraries</em> (LGPL gauges) so you can version,
			test, and publish instruments independently.
		</p>
		<div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
			<div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-6">
				<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-400">Live data</div>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
					Pinia store in <code class="text-cyan-300/80">@openattitude/core</code> subscribes to simulator
					properties with deadband hints—no hand-rolled polling.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-6">
				<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-400">Sharp SVG</div>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
					Instruments rasterize complex SVG faces for crisp scaling inside panel cutouts and fullscreen
					views.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-6 sm:col-span-2 lg:col-span-1">
				<div class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-400">Static deploy</div>
				<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
					Static builds suit GitHub Pages or any CDN—this site at
					<strong class="text-slate-300">www.openattitude.org</strong>, the live panel at
					<strong class="text-slate-300">senecaii.openattitude.org</strong>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

</SiteLayout>
